.container
  .row
    .col
      .container-fluid.text-center
        / .row
        /   .col
        /     %h1 #{dato.application.name}
        .row.justify-content-center
          / .col-4.col-lg-3
          #animated-text-container.col.mb-2
            %p
              %span Ruby
              %span Rails
            %p
              %span Rails
              %span Presenter
            %p
              %span Presenter
              %span Classes
        .row.justify-content-center.mt-4
          .col.col-lg-8
            = image_tag 'images/hero-title.png', class: 'img-fluid mb-3'
            %h3 It's time to beautify your Rails views
            %p
              MetaPresenter is a
              %strong 100% free
              Ruby gem that gives you access to the powerful presenter pattern in your Rails contollers. Pull yourself out of the vortex of messy Rails. Start writing beautiful frontend code that will streamline your work and &ldquo;wow&rdquo; your coworkers. 

        .row.justify-content-center
          .col.col-lg-4
            .instructions.text-left
              %p To install just add to your Gemfile, then bundle
              = code('ruby') do
                \# presenter classes for views
                gem 'meta_presenter' 
              = code('sh') do
                $ bundle install
        .row.justify-content-center
          .col.col-lg-4
            %p.upcase.learnmore Learn More

.container-fluid.container-light
  .row
    .col
      .container-fluid.text-center
        .row.justify-content-center
          .col.col-lg-8
            %h2.shadow.elegantshadow.upcase MetaPresenter
            %h3 How does it work?
            %p
              For each controller/action pair you get a controller class in app/presenters that you can use in your views with presenter.method_name. There's even a DSL for method delegation on objects to reduce boilerplate.

      %ul.container-fluid
        - dato.home.steps.each do |step|
          = partial 'selling_point', locals: {message: step.message, code_block: step.code, syntax_language: step.syntax_language}
        
      .container-fluid.text-center
        .row
          .col
            = link_to '/readme', class: 'btn btn-primary' do
              #{dato.home.start_button}
